{"url": "https://medium.com/@PepsRyuu/monorepos-in-javascript-anti-pattern-917603da59c8", "time": 1682993085.107649, "path": "medium.com/@PepsRyuu/monorepos-in-javascript-anti-pattern-917603da59c8/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Monorepos in JavaScript, Anti-Pattern | by Paul Sweeney | Medium", "h1": "Monorepos in JavaScript, Anti-Pattern", "description": "Something I\u2019ve noticed more lately, is this trend of having several npm micro-packages all contained in one repository. Many popular open-source projects adopt this pattern, React, Parcel, Babel, and\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [], "all_paragraphs": ["Something I\u2019ve noticed more lately, is this trend of having several npm micro-packages all contained in one repository. Many popular open-source projects adopt this pattern, React, Parcel, Babel, and many more. I would argue that in the majority of cases, this pattern is more detrimental to a project than a benefit, introducing unnecessary complexity at the cost of usability for both the author and the developer.", "Software Developer. Opinions are my own.", "Software Developer. Opinions are my own."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/@PepsRyuu?source=post_page-----917603da59c8--------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/@PepsRyuu?source=post_page-----917603da59c8--------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Paul Sweeney"}, {"url": "https://unsplash.com/@yancymin?utm_source=medium&utm_medium=referral", "anchor_text": "Yancy Min"}, {"url": "https://unsplash.com?utm_source=medium&utm_medium=referral", "anchor_text": "Unsplash"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/@PepsRyuu?source=post_page-----917603da59c8--------------------------------", "anchor_text": "More from Paul Sweeney"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?actionUrl=%2F_%2Fapi%2Fsubscriptions%2Fnewsletters%2F2d9b2fb95